# Caddyfile — HTTPS reverse proxy for Nodebook
#
# Replace "yourdomain.com" with your actual domain name.
# Caddy automatically obtains and renews a TLS certificate via Let's Encrypt.
# HTTP traffic is automatically redirected to HTTPS.
#
# Prerequisites:
#   - Your domain's DNS A record must point to this server's public IP.
#   - Ports 80 and 443 must be reachable from the internet.

yourdomain.com {
    reverse_proxy nodebook:3001
}
